<para id="fs-id2583910">Similarly, flavin adenine dinucleotide (FAD<sup>+</sup>) is derived from vitamin B<sub>2</sub>, also called riboflavin. Its reduced form is FADH<sub>2</sub>. A second variation of NAD, NADP, contains an extra phosphate group. Both NAD<sup>+</sup> and FAD<sup>+</sup> are extensively used in energy extraction from sugars, and NADP plays an important role in anabolic reactions and photosynthesis.</para>
